<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>This conversation excludes bowlers and genuine all rounders. </p> <p>Only speaking of batting all rounders, pure batters and keepers who should have bowled more. Frequency of having the ball in hand being less than that of Glenn Maxwell. </p> <p>Your reasoning can range from &quot;they had a nice action&quot; to &quot;they were better than given credit for&quot; to &quot;should have taken advantage of being captain&quot; or maybe they should have bowled more just for fun. </p> <p>My answer: Usman Khwaja.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/PupandPatsVC"> /u/PupandPatsVC </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/Cricket/comments/133gt6k/who_are_some_players_who_should_have_bowled_more/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/Cricket/comments/133gt6k/who_are_some_players_who_should_have_bowled_more/">[comments]</a></span>